data.enText: to be so full that the contents go over the sides

data.chText: 聚会上的食物碟满盘盈。

data.enText: to have too many people in it
The streets were overflowing with the crowds.
The hospitals are filled to overflowing (= with patients) .
to spread beyond the limits of a place or container that is too full

data.chText: 集会的人群延伸到了大街上。
data.enText: The meeting overflowed into the street.
a number of people or things that do not fit into the space available

data.chText: 新建了一座办公大楼以便容纳多出的员工。
data.enText: A new office block was built to accommodate the overflow of staff.
the action of liquid flowing out of a container, etc. that is already full; the liquid that flows out
an overflow of water from the lake
a pipe that allows extra liquid to escape

data.chText: 溢出，上溢（运算产生的数值位数或字的长度等超过存储单元的长度）
data.enText: a fault that happens because a number or data item (for example, the result of a calculation) is too large for the computer to represent it exactly

ex.chText: 聚会上的食物碟满盘盈。

synonyms.bx: 指某处的某物极多，达到或近乎达到泛滥、容纳不下的程度，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 北方有许许多多野生动物。
ex.enText: Wild animals abound in the north.

synonyms.bx: 指某物大量存在，比比皆是，数量惊人，常后接介词 in/with。

ex.enText: The shops were teeming with customers.
The lake is teeming with grass carp.

ex.chText: 她的头脑里好主意极多。
ex.enText: Good ideas teem in her head.

synonyms.bx: 指某地到处都是移动着的人、动物等，也可喻指某种事物数量极多，常用于 be teeming with sth 结构中。

ex.chText: 油从破裂的管子中喷射出来。
ex.enText: Oil gushed from the broken pipe.

ex.chText: 她头上的伤口大量出血。
ex.enText: Blood gushed from the wound in her head.

synonyms.bx: 指液体、气体、话语等大量涌出。

ex.chText: 雨水像瀑布般地从房顶上倾泻而下。
ex.enText: Rainwater cascaded down the roof of the house.

ex.chText: 大量硬币从吃角子老虎机中倾泻而出。
ex.enText: Coins cascaded from the fruit machine.

synonyms.bx: 指瀑布一般大量而快速地落下，可以是液体，也可以是其他东西。

ex.enText: Water flooded in through the back door.

synonyms.bx: 多指河流泛滥，也指人或物大量涌入某处。

ex.chText: 你注意到那些堆满塑料杯的垃圾箱了吗？
ex.enText: Did you notice the waste bins overflowing with plastic cups?

synonyms.bx: 指河、湖泛滥，或容器中的东西外溢。

tr: the occurrence of surplus liquid (as water) exceeding the limit or capacity

example: The children bubbled over with joy
My boss was bubbling over with anger

tr: flow or run over (a limit or brim)

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ˌəʊvə'fləʊ/. The noun is pronounced /'əʊvəfləʊ/. 动词读作 /ˌəʊvə'fləʊ/。名词读作 /'əʊvəfləʊ/。

value.def: If a liquid or a river overflows, it flows over the edges of the container or place it is in.

example.ex: Pour in some of the syrup, but not all of it, as it will probably overflow...
example.tran: 倒一些糖浆进去，但别全倒，因为可能会溢出来。

example.ex: Rivers and streams have overflowed their banks in countless places.
example.tran: 在许多地方，河流与小溪都已经决堤。

value.def: If a place or container is overflowing with people or things, it is too full of them.

example.ex: The great hall was overflowing with people...
Jails and temporary detention camps are overflowing...
example.tran: 监狱和临时拘留所里人满为患。

example.ex: He emptied a few overflowing ashtrays.
example.tran: 他将几只满满的烟灰缸倒干净。

value.def: If someone is overflowing with a feeling or if the feeling overflows, the person is experiencing it very strongly and shows this in their behaviour.

example.ex: Kenneth overflowed with friendliness and hospitality...
example.tran: 肯尼思满怀友善好客之情。
里德利终于按捺不住满腔的怒火。

value.tran: 洋溢着（情感）；（情感）溢于言表

value.def: The overflow is the extra people or things that something cannot contain or deal with because it is not large enough.

example.ex: Tents have been set up next to hospitals to handle the overflow...
example.tran: 医院旁搭起了帐篷以安置容纳不下的人员。

example.ex: The loch's overflow cascades into the waterfalls of a Japanese water garden.
example.tran: 溢出的湖水倾泻而下，形成了一座日式水景花园的瀑布。

value.tran: （过多而）容纳不下的人（或东西）

value.def: An overflow is a hole or pipe through which liquid can flow out of a container when it gets too full.
If a place or container is filled to overflowing, it is so full of people or things that no more can fit in.

example.ex: The kitchen garden was full to overflowing with fresh vegetables...
example.tran: 家庭菜园里种满了新鲜蔬菜。

example.ex: He was one of the few teachers who always filled the lecture room to overflowing.
example.tran: 他是为数不多的课堂场场爆满的老师之一。
